In this tutorial, you will learn how to build a simple to-do list application using React. We'll cover everything from setting up the environment to styling the app to making it feel more interactive. The code snippets provided can be followed step-by-step to build the application.

## Prerequisites

Before following this tutorial, ensure you have the following installed:
- Node.js and npm (Node Package Manager)
- A code editor (optional but recommended)

## Step 1: Setting Up the Environment

1. Open your terminal or command prompt.

2. Create a new React project by running:
   ```bash
   npx create-react-app todo-list-app
   ```

3. Change into the project directory:
